With relation to the moderator's comment that the putative viral agent responsible for wobbly possum disease [WPD] "has not been positively identified and characterised," I'd like to point the readers to our recent publication (Dunowska et al, Vet Micro, 2011: http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/j.vetmic.2011.11.013, in which we have shown the initial data suggesting that the WPD virus is a novel nidovirus, most closely related to the members of the current family Arteriviridae.

--
